-- ConocoPhillips raises share buyback plan, dividend
-- 
-- Fri Feb 9, 2007 1:48pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/09/businesspro-conocophillips-buyback-dc-idUSWNAS045720070209

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - ConocoPhillips ( COP.N ) plans to buy 
back up to $4 billion of its stock in 2007 and will raise its 
quarterly dividend 14 percent, the No. 3 U.S. oil company said 
on Friday. 


  The company said the $4 billion share repurchase plan 
includes the $1 billion of stock buybacks it announced earlier 
in the year. It said it plans to buy back about $1 billion of 
its shares in the first quarter.